<h2 id="bsc-eqn">Basic equation</h2>
<p>In the CMA-ES, a population of new search points (individual, offspring) is generated by sampling a MVN, in which for generation number $g$, for $g=0,1,2,\ldots$
\begin{equation}
\mathbf{x}_k^{(g+1)}\sim\mathbf{m}^{(g)}+\sigma^{(g)}\mathcal{N}(\mathbf{0},\mathbf{C}^{(g)}),\hspace{1cm}k=1,\ldots,\lambda
\end{equation}
where</p>
<ul>
  <li>$\mathbf{x}_k^{(g+1)}\in\mathbb{R}^n$ is the $k$-th offspring from generation $g+1$</li>
  <li>$\mathbf{m}^{(g)}$</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="references">References</h2>
